ight=\"282\" /></p>\r\nThese promises that are made by contractors are usually made in the hope that you will just trust them and not worry to look for a cheaper deal.  In the chance you do find a lower price and present it to them, I find that the contractors will install cheap products and use unskilled labor as a way to beat this lower price you have found. Our promise to you is that \"we will use the highest quality products, installed by well educated electricians, in a safe and craftsman like manner, and at a competitive rate.\"\r\n\r\nEazy Electric has a low overhead that allows for our prices to be lower without compromising the quality of our installations or the products we install.\r\n\r\nWe can give quick estimates for most small projects right over the phone!  To help us give you the most accurate quote please have ready the information in the request a quote drop down on the home page.  Or if you prefer please feel free to fill out the form and send it in and we will get back to you within twenty four hours.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to serving you and earning your trust!', 'Pricing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-13', '', '', '2011-02-17 05:52:51', '2011-02-17 05:52:51', '', '36', 'http://eazyelectric.com/36-revision-13/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('100', '1', '2011-02-13 03:37:56', '2011-02-13 03:37:56', '<a href=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/01/hard_hat_icon.png\"><img title=\"hard_hat_icon\" src=\"../wp-content/uploads/2011/01/hard_hat_icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"95\" height=\"84\" /></a>These are a few of the many Electrical Services that we provide:\r\n\r\nTroubleshooting\r\n\r\nService Panel Upgrades\r\n\r\nSubpanels\r\n\r\nHot tub hookups\r\n\r\nFire Alarm Systems\r\n\r\nNew circuits\r\n\r\nExtending circuits\r\n\r\nSwitch and Receptacle upgrades\r\n\r\nIndoor lighting\r\n\r\nLandscape lighting\r\n\r\nSolar Power/Photovoltaic systems\r\n\r\nGenerators\r\n\r\nHeatpumps\r\n\r\nTelecomunications\r\n\r\nHome Theater Sytems', 'Services', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-6', '', '', '2011-02-13 03:37:56', '2011-02-13 03:37:56', '', '13', 'http://eazyelectric.dev/13-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('101', '1', '2011-02-13 03:43:45', '2011-02-13 03:43:45', '<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>Why do recepticle outlets just stop working?</strong></em></span> Receptacles are simple devices that over time, or through manufacturer defect sometimes simply break, and need to be replaced.  Another possible answer is that from over time the wires that bring power to the receptacle have expanded and contracted from the heat produced when current flows through it.  This makes the wires brittle and the electrical bond can be lost through this process.  This could be a potentially dangerous situation and should not be ignored.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>My light does not turn on anymore?</strong></em></span> Like receptacles, light switches are simple devices that over time or through manufacturer error tend to break.  After checking to see if the switch truly is the problem and we find it to be working properly, we will check the wiring that is attached to the fixture;  making sure that there is a quality splice.\r\n\r\nSome light fixtures contain ballasts, which is basically the brains of the fixture, and they too over time seem to go bad.  In most cases we can just replace the ballast without having to install a new fixture.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>The Breaker keeps tripping?</strong></em></span> Circuit breakers also are simple devices that due to time or poor quality can stop functioning properly and need to be replaced. More commonly I seem to find that the circuit that is being protected by this breaker is overloaded.  This is because older homes were not designed to supply the various appliances that we so', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-8', '', '',