65', 'Contact Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'contact-us', '', '', '2012-07-30 05:34:13', '2012-07-30 05:34:13', '', '0', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/?page_id=152', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('149', '1', '2011-02-17 05:50:05', '2011-02-17 05:50:05', 'There are a few things to consider when you purchase a hot tub.  Give us a call and we\'ll help get you relaxin\' in no time.', 'Hot Tub Hookup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '62-revision-3', '', '', '2011-02-17 05:50:05', '2011-02-17 05:50:05', '', '62', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/62-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('150', '1', '2011-04-21 18:51:36', '2011-04-21 18:51:36', 'I\'ll admit I knew becoming a electrician in Seattle was going to involve crawling around in boiling hot attics with itchy insulation ending up everywhere on me, like sand after a day at the beach.  Then there\'s the awesome smell of dead rats and other lovely little critters I find in the crawl spaces under houses that can put a damper on my day as an electrical contractor.  But I will say that I don\'t mind it as much when I know that at the end of the day I am providing a service that will bring my customer a truly relaxing experience!  I love my Hot Tub and I look forward to helping you enjoy yours as well.\r\n\r\nThere are a few important things to consider while planning your hot tub install:\r\n\r\n1.)  The further away from the main electrical panels in your home that you place the hot tub will add to the cost in this service due to the recent high prices in copper wire.  Eazy Electric works with the main Seattle electrical wholesalers to get you the best price on all your material.\r\n\r\n2.)  Are you able and willing to help with the installation?  Some customers have preferred to do the required digging for the conduit that runs from the house to where the Spa will rest.  This will reduce the work for electricians and will save you money.\r\n\r\n3.)  Be sure to ask when purchasing your Spa if the electrical disconnect comes with it or if you have to purchase this separate.  If the disconnect is included make sure to ask for it from the ones delivering the spa.  I say this as they run about $100 and the people delivering my tub tried to keep it!\r\n\r\n4.)  Be aware that it is a code requirement to have a receptacle outlet located not less than 6 feet from, and not more than 20 feet from, the inside wall of the spa.  This is a quick fix if your home does not currently have one.\r\n\r\n5.)  Eazy Electric is one of the few Seattle electrical contractors that offer on site planning of your Spa install at no cost.  We say this because this project can become complicated and we want to ensure that your relaxing in your spa as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n6.)  Installing a hot tub is a dangerous job.  There is some residential work that any do-it-your self-er can handle, but I would encourage you to hire a qualified electrician for this project.', 'Hot Tub Hookup: Things to consider', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '62-revision-4', '', '', '2011-04-21 18:51:36', '2011-04-21 18:51:36', '', '62', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/62-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('153', '1', '2011-04-28 19:21:03', '2011-04-28 19:21:03', 'Phone:\n\n(360) 620-8829.\n\nEmail:\n<a href=\"mailto:erik@eazyelectric.com\">erik@eazyelectric.com</a>\n\nMail:\nP.O. Box 25353\nSeattle, WA 98165', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '152-revision', '', '', '2011-04-28 19:21:03', '2011-04-28 19:21:03', '', '152', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/152-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('151', '1', '2011-04-23 01:12:07', '2011-04-23 01:12:07', 'There are a few important things to consider while planning your hot tub install:\r\n\r\n1.)  The further away from the main electrical panels in your home that you place the hot tub will add to the cost in this service due to the recent high prices in copper wire.  Eazy Electric works with the main Seattle electrical wholesalers to get you the best price on all your material.\r\n\r\n2.)  Are you able and willing to help with the installation?  Some customers have preferred to do the required digging for the conduit that runs from the house to where the Spa will rest.  This will reduce the work for electricians and will save you money.\r\n\r\n3.)  Be sure to ask when purchasing your Spa if the electrical disconnect comes with it or if you have to purchase this separate.  If the disconnect is included make sure to ask for it from the ones delivering the spa.  I say this as they run about $100 and the people delivering my tub tried to keep it!\r\n\r\n4.)  Be aware that it is a code requirement to have a receptacle outlet located not less than 6 feet from, and not more than 20 feet from, the inside wall of the spa.  This is a quick fix if your home does not currently have one.\r\n\r\n5.)  Eazy Electric is one of the few Seattle electrical contractors that offer on site planning of your Spa install at no cost.  We say this because this project can become complicated and we want to ensure that your relaxing in your spa as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n6.)  Installing a hot tub is a dangerous job.  There is some residential work that any do-it-your self-er can handle, but I would encourage you to hire a qualified electrician for this project.\r\n\r\nI\'ll admit I knew becoming a electrician in Seattle was going to involve  crawling around in boiling hot attics with itchy insulation ending up  everywhere on me, like sand after a day at the beach.  Then there\'s the  awesome smell of dead rats and other lovely little critters I find in  the crawl spaces under houses that can put a damper on my day as an  electrical contractor.  But I will say that I don\'t mind it as much when  I know that at the end of the day I am providing a service that will  bring my customer a truly relaxing experience!\r\n\r\nI love my hot tub and I  look forward to helping you enjoy yours as well.', 'Hot Tub Hookup: Things to consider', '', 