, '', '66', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/66-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('170', '1', '2011-02-17 05:56:19', '2011-02-17 05:56:19', 'GUARANTEED LOWEST PRICE!!!  WE\'LL BEAT ANY WRITTEN OFFER!!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-113 alignright\" title=\"cheezy sales guy\" src=\"http://eazyelectric.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/iStock_000005487266XSmall.jpg\" alt=\"eazy electric won\'t do this to you\" width=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nThese promises that are made by contractors are usually made in the hope that you will just trust them and not worry to look for a cheaper deal.  In the chance you do find a lower price and present it to them, I find that the contractors will install cheap products and use unskilled labor as a way to beat this lower price you have found. Our promise to you is that \"we will use the highest quality products, installed by well educated electricians, in a safe and craftsman like manner, and at a competitive rate.\"\r\n\r\nEazy Electric has a low overhead that allows for our prices to be lower without compromising the quality of our installations or the products we install.\r\n\r\nWe can give quick estimates for most small projects right over the phone!  To help us give you the most accurate quote please have ready the information in the request a quote drop down on the home page.  Or if you prefer please feel free to fill out the form and send it in and we will get back to you within twenty four hours.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to serving you and earning your trust!', 'Pricing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-18', '', '', '2011-02-17 05:56:19', '2011-02-17 05:56:19', '', '36', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/36-revision-18/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('171', '1', '2011-02-17 05:46:48', '2011-02-17 05:46:48', '<a href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/service_panel1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-109\" title=\"service_panel\" src=\"http://eazyelectric.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/service_panel1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"174\" height=\"261\" /></a>Does your service panel look something like this?  That\'s when you know you need to call in a professional.', 'Service Panel Changes / Upgrades', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-7', '', '', '2011-02-17 05:46:48', '2011-02-17 05:46:48', '', '15', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/15-revision-7/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('172', '1', '2011-09-13 23:33:34', '2011-09-13 23:33:34', 'Service Panel changes and upgrades are our specialty!\r\n\r\nMany homes today, including mine, were built many years ago when there was considerably less available electric equipment such as microwaves, large entertainment equipment, hot-tubs, ect.  With all of these added conveniences we unwittingly put ourselves in danger of overloading our electrical service.  Just like only so much water can be forced down a pipe before it burst, so is electricity running through the wiring in your home.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What Benefits Are There To Upgrading My Service?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n1.)  By upgrading your service you will have more peace knowing that the heart of your electrical system is safe.\r\n\r\n2.)  Our new panels that we install will also give you room to grow, with the added spaces they provide for future circuits.\r\n\r\n3.)  The electrical grounding for your home, which is paramount to your safety, will be brought up to code per NEC requirements.\r\n\r\n4.)  The circuits will be clearly marked for your convieniece in case a circuit breaker trips.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>How Do I Know I Need A New Electrical Panel?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n1.)  A good place to start is to look at the manufacturer of your electrical panel.  There are two brands in particular that should be aggressivley dealt with and they are: Federal Pacific Electric (FPE), and Zinzsco.  These two brands are responsible for many fires as there equipment fails to turn off when needed.  We encourage you research for yourself online what the dangers are of these panel types.\r\n\r\n2.)  If your panel still uses the screw-in type fuses to protect your circuits.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Service Panel Changes / Upgrades', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-8', '', '', '2011-09-13 23:33:34', '2011-09-13 23:33:34', '', '15', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/15-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('194', '1', '2011-09-14 00:39:50', '2011-09-14 00:39:50', '<strong>Service Panel changes and upgrades are our specialty!</strong>\r\n\r\nMany homes today, including mine, were built many years ago when there was considerably less available electric equipment such as microwaves, large entertainment equipment, hot-tubs, ect.  With all of these added conveniences we unwittingly put ourselves in danger of overloading our electrical service.  Just like only so much water can be forced down a pipe before it burst, so is electricity running through the wiring in your home.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What Benefits Are There To Upgrading My Service?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n1.)  By upgrading your service you will have more peace knowing that the heart of your electrical system is safe.\r\n\r\n2.)  Our new panels that we install will also give you room to grow, with the added spaces they provide for future circuits.\r\n\r\n3.)  The electrical grounding for your home, which is paramount to your safety, will be brought up to code per NEC requirements.\r\n\r\n4.)  The circuits will be clearly marked for your convenience in case a circuit breaker trips.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>How Do I Know I Need A New Electrical Panel?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n1.)  A good place to start is to look at the manufacturer of your electrical panel.  There are two brands in particular that should be aggressively dealt with and they are: Federal Pacific Electric (FPE), and Zinsco.  These two brands are responsible for many fires as there equipment fails to turn off when needed.  We encourage you research for yourself online what the dangers are of these panel types.\r\n\r\n2.)  If your panel still uses the screw-in type fuses to protect your circuits.\r\n\r\n3.)  If your adding large equipment to your existing panel i.e. heating elements, spa, ect\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What Can I Expect?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n1.)  First we will come out and talk to you about your project, as each system will be different.  At this time we will show you what to expect during the project, and determine if you actually need a panel upgrade.  In some instances we are able to rearrange things in your panel, which will allow you to accomplish your goal without the hassle and expense of upgrading your electrical service.\r\n\r\n2.)  Next we will send you an estimate that will include the minimum requirements for your project, and also any options we discussed during the walk-through.  The estimate will include all permitting and taxes for your area.  Be aware most companies don\'t provide this until the end hoping that you\'ll just look at the initial figure to win your approval.  Permitting and taxes on a project this size can easily be in the hundreds of dollars!  We will let you know from the beginning what to expect.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Service Panel Changes / Upgrades', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-10', '', '', '2011-09-14 00:39:50', '2011-09-14 00:39:50', '', '15', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/15-revision-10/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('173', '1', '2011-09-13 23:34:28', '2011-09-13 23:34:28', 'Service Panel changes and upgrades are our specialty!\r\n\r\nMany homes today, including mine, were built many years ago when there was considerably less available electric equipment such as microwaves, large entertainment equipment, hot-tubs, ect.  With all of these added conveniences we unwittingly put ourselves in danger of ov