replacing faulty equipment.  We stock many items in our service vehicles to reduce the time it takes going to the supply stores.  To help reduce these trips please fill out the <a href=\"/request-quote/\">request a quote</a> page with as much detail as possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Troubleshooting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'troubleshooting', '', '', '2012-05-29 15:53:18', '2012-05-29 15:53:18', '', '13', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/?page_id=218', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('190', '1', '2011-02-19 00:53:52', '2011-02-19 00:53:52', 'These are a few of the many Electrical Services that we provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Troubleshooting</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"service panel changes and upgrades\" href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/services/service-panels/\">Service Panel Upgrades</a></li>\r\n	<li>Sub-panels</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"hot tub installation\" href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/services/hot-tub-hookup/\">Hot tub hookups</a></li>\r\n	<li>Fire Alarm Systems</li>\r\n	<li>New circuits</li>\r\n	<li>Extending circuits</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"outlet upgrades and changes\" href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/services/switch-receptable-upgrades/\">Switch and Receptacle upgrades</a></li>\r\n	<li>Indoor lighting</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"landscape garden lighting installation\" href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/services/landscape-lighting/\">Landscape lighting</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"solar power installation\" href=\"http://eazyelectric.com/services/solar-power-photovoltaic-systems/\">Solar Power/Photovoltaic systems</a></li>\r\n	<li>Generators</li>\r\n	<li>Heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Home Theater Systems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAnd many more...', 'Services', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-12', '', '', '2011-02-19 00:53:52', '2011-02-19 00:53:52', '', '13', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/13-revision-12/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('192', '1', '2011-06-27 23:16:12', '2011-06-27 23:16:12', '<strong>There are a few important things to consider while planning your hot tub install:</strong>\r\n\r\n1.)  <strong>Are you able and willing to help with the installation?</strong> Some customers have preferred to do the required digging for the conduit that runs from the house to where the Spa will rest.  This will reduce the work for electricians and will save you money.\r\n\r\n2.)  <strong>Be sure to ask when purchasing your Spa if the electrical disconnect comes with it or if you have to purchase this separate. </strong> If the disconnect is included make sure to ask for it from the ones delivering the spa.  I say this as they run about $100 and the people delivering my tub tried to keep it!\r\n\r\n3.)  <strong>Be aware that it is a code requirement to have a receptacle outlet located not less than 6 feet from, and not more than 20 feet from, the inside wall of the spa.</strong> This is a quick fix if your home does not currently have one.\r\n\r\n4.) <strong> Installing a hot tub is a dangerous job.</strong> There is some residential work that any do-it-your self-er can handle, but I would encourage you to hire a qualified electrician for this project.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nI\'ll admit I knew becoming a electrician in Seattle was going to involve  crawling around in boiling hot attics with itchy insulation ending up  everywhere on me, like sand after a day at the beach.  Then there\'s the  awesome smell of dead rats and other lovely little critters I find in  the crawl spaces under houses that can put a damper on my day as an  electrical contractor.  But I will say that I don\'t mind it as much when  I know that at the end of the day I am providing a service that will  bring my customer a truly relaxing experience!\r\n\r\n<em>\"I love my hot tub and I  look forward to helping you enjoy yours as well.\"</em>', 'Hot Tub Hookup: Things to consider', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '62-revision-11', '', '', '2011-06-27 23:16:12', '2011-06-27 23:16:12', '', '62', 'http://www.eazyelectric.com/62-revision-11/', '0